<p>Russia has blocked access to WhatsApp and, in recent days, has also blocked or limited Telegram. The moves extend a broader effort to control which online services people can reach inside the country. Russian officials say the action is tied to compliance with Russian legislation. The restrictions hit everyday communication at scale. WhatsApp has more than 100 million users in Russia, and authorities have promoted “Max,” a domestic messaging service, as an alternative.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/qLeYEbMVfHBFvIYeqRjU9qjTxOgVIIXGqe-KPC4_uzX-0OV2wSs5Tg-PEvPCy4rRRy_xeV3J9eLADwKJOY4kcKrr5m_Q40ugtG4BkrTR6uhR' alt='An illustration photo shows WhatsApp’s logo on a smartphone screen in Moscow (April 11, 2023).' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Wider clampdown: DW says the squeeze goes beyond messaging. Other major services, including YouTube, have also become inaccessible in Russia, adding to uncertainty about what will remain available online.</li><li>Workarounds: As the list of blocked services grows, users are looking for ways to bypass government restrictions to keep using banned apps and websites.</li><li>Official push: NDTV reports the Kremlin urged WhatsApp users to switch to a domestic “national messenger,” reinforcing the promotion of Max as the alternative.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Kremlin (Dmitry Peskov): Peskov said WhatsApp’s owner must comply with Russian law for the service to be unblocked, according to state media cited in reporting. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/technology/whatsapp-says-russia-attempted-to-fully-block-app/article70622851.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>WhatsApp: WhatsApp said Russia has tried to fully block the app, calling it an attempt to steer people toward a state-owned, surveillance-style alternative. (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/russia-blocks-whatsapp-as-it-pushes-state-backed-alternative-on-citizens/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>Russian authorities: Officials said the blocks and restrictions stem from alleged non-compliance with Russian legislation, including demands for data access in law-enforcement investigations. (<a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/russia-is-cracking-down-on-whatsapp-and-telegram.-here%27s-what-we-know'>Japan Today</a>)</li><li>Activists/critics: Activists and critics say Max could become a surveillance tool, and argue the restrictions fit a wider campaign to tighten control over internet use. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1972880/russia-blocks-whatsapp-and-telegram'>Dawn</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/russia-blocks-youtube-and-whatsapp/a-75940102'>Russia blocks YouTube and WhatsApp</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/russia-is-cracking-down-on-whatsapp-and-telegram.-here%27s-what-we-know'>Russia cracking down on WhatsApp and Telegram</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/russia-confirms-ban-on-whatsapp-says-it-failed-to-abide-by-law-10993914#publisher=newsstand'>Russia Bans WhatsApp, Wants Citizens To Use &#x27;National Messenger&#x27; Instead</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/russia-blocks-whatsapp-as-it-pushes-state-backed-alternative-on-citizens/'>Russia blocks WhatsApp as it pushes state-backed alternative on citizens</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/technology/whatsapp-says-russia-attempted-to-fully-block-app/article70622851.ece'>WhatsApp says Russia has tried to fully block the messaging app</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1972880/russia-blocks-whatsapp-and-telegram'>Russia blocks WhatsApp and Telegram</a> - dawn.com</li></ul>